The paper deals with the problem of jointly optimizing modulation and estimation of a random parameter over a noisy channel, which is a classic problem in information theory (cs.IT). The focus is on the large deviations behavior of the estimator, which is a topic of interest in statistical inference (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of quantization and channel coding, which are common techniques in multimedia communication (cs.MM) and networked systems (cs.NI). Finally, the paper provides insights into the behavior of the estimation error for multidimensional parameter vectors, which is relevant to machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG).
